DIAGNOSIS. — Shells small (<
10 mm
), subcircular, inflated, with prominent radial ribs (up to 35) crossed by regularly spaced, very thin, commarginal lamellae. Radial ribs obsolete at posterior dorsal margin. Lunule heart-shaped to lanceolate, symmetrical. Hinge teeth small, LV with anterior lateral, 2 cardinal teeth and posterior lateral; RV with anterior lateral, a single cardinal and posterior lateral. Anterior adductor muscle scar short, slightly detached from pallial line. Interior shell margin coarsely crenulate.

Liralucina sperabilis
(
Hedley, 1909
)

n. comb.
(
Figs 25
; 
26A
)
